{0 Pixeldrift {%html: <span class="version">%%VERSION%%</span>%}}

Pixeldrift finds perceptible pixel differences between two equally
sized sRGB images with an alpha component. It is mostly suitable for
comparing synthetic images: diagrams, user interface screenshots,
rendering algorithms outputs, etc.

